# App Router

- Use App Router (`app/`); no Pages Router.
- **Server Components by default**; `"use client"` only for state, effects, browser APIs, or event handlers.
- No premature API routes — data fetching comes later via Server Components or Route Handlers.

## Layouts and pages

- Shared shell in `app/(app)/layout.tsx`.
- Pages stay thin: composition only, no large inline UI blocks.
- Route Handlers (later): `app/api/**/route.ts` with typed request/response.

## Example

```tsx
// Page: composition (server component)
export default function ReflectiePage() {
  return <ReflectieForm />;
}

// Client only where needed
"use client";
export function ReflectieForm() {
  // state + event handlers
}
```

## Next.js 16

APIs may differ from older versions. Consult `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` when in doubt.
